002669r 2               ; SYM_FUNC: emit args, then MRKA + CALL.  Result is left on TOS by op_RETF.
002669r 2               ; expr_type is the function's return type (already set).
002669r 2               ; X=off lo, scratch=off hi, top of 6502 stack = pcount.
002669r 2               ; NOTE: still not nest-safe inside one arg expression — fcall_pcount and
002669r 2               ; fcall_vmask live in zero-page across the loop and a nested function-call
002669r 2               ; arg would clobber them.  Pre-existing limitation; tracked as TODO.
002669r 2               ;
002669r 2               ; Args are evaluated BEFORE MRKA so LDL/LDA_L inside arg expressions
002669r 2               ; addresses the caller's MP (not the callee's).  MRKA then shifts the
002669r 2               ; pcount pushed values up by AR_LOCALS into local slots 0..pcount-1.
002669r 2               ;
002669r 2               ; lsize_extra is computed up-front and stashed on the 6502 hw stack so
002669r 2               ; record-field lookup inside an arg (which scratches fcall_lsize) cannot
002669r 2               ; corrupt the MRKA operand we emit at the end.
